&lt;li&gt;A/V &amp;amp; Meeting Support: Ensure all Executive-led meetings and board presentations run flawlessly by managing and proactive testing of A/V systems and conference room technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Device Management: Execute the deployment, imaging, and maintenance of all Executive hardware, ensuring devices are always up-to-date, secure, and performing optimally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User Lifecycle: Manage the seamless onboarding and off boarding of Executive staff, including identity management, hardware provisioning, and personalized 1-on-1 training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compliance &amp;amp; Privacy: Strictly follow SOX, ISO, and internal privacy protocols, handling sensitive executive data with the highest level of confidentiality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Infrastructure Assistance: Assist the broader IT team with physical hardware installations (servers, racks, etc.) while prioritizing Executive-facing environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What You Need&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 3+ years of IT support experience, with at least 1 year specifically supporting Executives or high-profile users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability: Ability to work 5 days onsite at our HQ; must be flexible to provide support aligned with Executive schedules and occasional travel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel:&amp;nbsp; Occasional domestic and international travel required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Skills: Proficiency in Mac/PC environments, mobile device management (MDM), and enterprise A/V solutions (e.g., Zoom Rooms, Slack, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication: Exceptional interpersonal skills and the ability to remain calm and professional under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discretion: A proven track record of handling confidential information with integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical Ability: Ability to move and lift IT equipment (up to 50 lbs) as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
